---
layout: default
permalink: /spec/index.html
stylesheets:
  - spec
title: JMAP Specifications
description: >-
    The specifications for the core JMAP protocol and access to mail and
    contacts stores using JMAP have been finalised and published.
hero:
    eyebrow: Specifications
    eyebrow_icon: code-bracket
    title: JMAP RFC
    sub: >-
        The specifications for the core JMAP protocol and access to mail and
        contacts stores using JMAP have been finalised and published. The JMAP 
        working group is currently working on the calendars specs.
    links:
        - href: https://datatracker.ietf.org/wg/jmap/about/
          label: JMAP working group
specs:
    - label: Core
      description: >-
          These specifications define the core sync protocol and extensions
          that 
          are useful no matter what data type you might be syncing.
      items:
          - title: The core JMAP protocol
            eyebrow: RFC 8620
            href: /spec/rfc8620/
            body: >-
                Defines the generic JMAP protocol for efficiently querying,
                fetching, and modifying JSON data, with push notifications and
                fast resync.
          - title: VAPID for JMAP Push
            eyebrow: RFC 9749
            href: /spec/rfc9749/
            body: >-
                Lets JMAP servers advertise their ability to authenticate Web
                Push notifications using the Voluntary Application Server ID
                protocol.
          - title: JMAP Sharing
            eyebrow: RFC 9670
            href: /spec/rfc9670/
            body: >-
                Defines a reusable data model for sharing data between users in
                JMAP, providing a consistent base for other data types to build
                on.
          - title: JMAP via WebSocket
            eyebrow: RFC 8887
            href: /spec/rfc8887/
            body: >-
                Binds JMAP to a WebSocket transport layer, providing higher
                performance than the standard HTTP binding for connected
                clients.
          - title: JMAP Quotas
            eyebrow: RFC 9425
            href: /spec/rfc9425/
            body: >-
                Defines a data model for reading and syncing account quotas
                over JMAP, so clients can surface storage and message-count
                limits.
          - title: JMAP Blob Management
            eyebrow: RFC 9404
            href: /spec/rfc9404/
            body: >-
                Extends JMAP with inline blob creation and access via method
                calls, plus a reverse lookup to find where blobs are referenced
                in other data.
    - label: Mail
      description: >-
          This spec is not yet final and may change before publication. If you 
          find any issues, please email [jmap@ietf.org](mailto:jmap@ietf.org) or
          make a pull request on GitHub if you have a proposed fix.
      items:
          - title: JMAP Mail
            eyebrow: RFC 8621
            href: /spec/rfc8621/
            body: >-
                Defines the JMAP data model for email, letting clients
                efficiently search, access, organise, and send messages with
                push-based sync.
          - title: JMAP Sieve Scripts Management
            eyebrow: RFC 9661
            href: /spec/rfc9661/
            body: >-
                Defines a JMAP data model for managing Sieve scripts on a
                server, so clients can efficiently search, access, organise,
                and validate them.
          - title: JMAP MDN Handling
            eyebrow: RFC 9007
            href: /spec/rfc9007/
            body: >-
                Defines a JMAP data model for Message Disposition
                Notifications, enabling read-receipt workflows to be handled
                alongside regular mail.
          - title: JMAP S/MIME Signature Verification
            eyebrow: RFC 9219
            href: /spec/rfc9219/
            body: >-
                Extends JMAP Mail so servers can return the S/MIME signature
                verification status of messages alongside the rest of the
                message data.
    - label: Contacts and calendars
      items:
          - title: JMAP Contacts
            eyebrow: RFC 9610
            href: /spec/rfc9610/
            body: >-
                Defines the JMAP data model for contacts, letting clients
                synchronise address book data with a server using push-based
                updates.
          - title: JMAP Calendars
            eyebrow: In progress
            href: /spec/calendars-draft/
            class: card--in-progress
            body: >-
                A JMAP data model for calendar sync, letting clients read,
                write, and share calendars and events with push notifications
                and reminders.
    - label: Data formats
      description: >-
          JMAP was designed in conjunction with new JSON-based file formats for 
          contacts and calendars, which can also be used standalone or in other
          protocols.
      items:
          - title: JSContact
            eyebrow: RFC 9553
            href: /spec/rfc9553/
            body: >-
                A JSON data model for contact cards, designed as an
                unambiguous, extensible alternative to vCard for address book
                storage and exchange.
          - title: JSCalendar 2.0
            eyebrow: In progress
            href: /spec/jscalendar-draft/
            class: card--in-progress
            body: >-
                Version 2.0 of the JSON data model for calendar data, improving
                interoperability with iCalendar and aligning conventions with
                JSContact.
---
{%
    include components/hero.liquid
    eyebrow=page.hero.eyebrow
    eyebrow_icon=page.hero.eyebrow_icon
    title=page.hero.title
    sub=page.hero.sub
    links=page.hero.links
%}
{%- for section in page.specs -%}
    <section class='section section--spec'>
        <div class='u-wrapper'>
            <h2 class='section__title u-text-2xl u-font-bold'>{{ section.label }}</h2>
            {%- if section.description -%}
                <div class='section__description'>
                    {{ section.description | markdownify }}
                </div>
            {%- endif -%}
            <hr class='section__hr'>
            <ul class='section__cards card-grid'>
                {%- for item in section.items -%}
                    {%
                        include components/link-card.liquid
                        eyebrow=item.eyebrow
                        title=item.title
                        body=item.body
                        href=item.href
                        class=item.class
                    %}
                {% endfor %}
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>
{% endfor %}
